&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A ctive Voice में&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;, एक वाक्य विषय पर जोर देता है, एक क्रिया करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice में&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;, एक वाक्य वाक्य की क्रिया या वस्तु पर जोर देता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;active voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है और यह&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;future simple tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;जब हम इस वाक्य को&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलते हैं, तो&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;active voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Nobody&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object &amp;#39;anybody&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;बन जाता है&amp;nbsp;और&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object &amp;#39;you&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;बन जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active format&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;will + V1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;help&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; को&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive format&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;will + be + V3 (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;helped&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;में परिवर्तित किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यह&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;future simple tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;के लिए&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;active and passive voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rule&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;अतः सही उत्तर&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;within my visit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;i.e.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;this part of the sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;has an error&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, the use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;incorrect&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;not outside the limits of somebody or something&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;visit&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in the sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indicates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;going to see a person or place for a period of time&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;during&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;should be used&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in place of&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;during&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;within the period of time mentioned&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I saw several French colonial villas &lt;strong&gt;during my visit&lt;/strong&gt; to Puducherry&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का प्रयोग गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का अर्थ है किसी व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या वस्&amp;zwj;तु की &lt;strong&gt;सीमा के अंदर या भीतर&lt;/strong&gt;।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;वाक्य में &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;visit&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; शब्द का प्रयोग, किसी व्यक्ति या स्थान को कुछ समय के लिए देखने जाने का संकेत देता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;during&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का प्रयोग &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;within&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; के स्थान पर किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Preposition &amp;#39;during&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का अर्थ है &lt;strong&gt;के दौरान, की अवधि तक, निर्दिष्ट कालावधि में&lt;/strong&gt;।&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;अतः सही उत्तर&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;सही वाक्य:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I saw several French colonial villas&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;during my visit&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to Puducherry&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scarcely had she&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the underlined segment, the use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;No sooner&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;incorrect&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;No sooner&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; is &lt;strong&gt;followed by &amp;#39;than&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adverbials &lt;strong&gt;hardly, scarcely, barely, and no sooner&lt;/strong&gt; are often used &lt;strong&gt;to emphasize that one event quickly followed another&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbials&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hardly, scarcely,&lt;/strong&gt; and&lt;strong&gt; barely&lt;/strong&gt; are &lt;strong&gt;followed by&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;when&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, If&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hardly, scarcely, barely&lt;/span&gt;, and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;no sooner&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are in the initial position, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;auxiliary&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(here,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; had she&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;Scarcely&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;should be used&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in place of&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;No sooner&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scarcely had she&lt;/strong&gt; put the baby to sleep when a loud noise woke him up&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;रेखांकित खण्ड में &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;No sooner&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का प्रयोग गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Negative adverbial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;No sooner&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; के बाद &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;than&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; आता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adverbials&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hardly, scarcely, barely,&lt;/span&gt; और &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;no sooner&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;इस बात पर जोर देने के लिए कि एक घटना दूसरे के तुरंत बाद आती है।।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Negative adverbials&lt;/span&gt; - &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hardly, scarcely,&lt;/span&gt; और &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;barely,&lt;/span&gt; के बाद &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;when&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; आता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसके अलावा, &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hardly, scarcely, barely&lt;/span&gt;, और&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;no sooner&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;प्रारंभिक स्थिति में&amp;nbsp;हैं, तो &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&lt;/span&gt; और &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;auxiliary&lt;/span&gt; उलटे होते हैं (यहाँ, &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;had she&lt;/span&gt;)।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;No sooner&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative adverbial &amp;#39;Scarcely&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;अतः सही उत्तर&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;सही वाक्य:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Scarcely had she&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;put the baby to sleep when a loud noise woke him up&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;ACEBDF&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumble question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting off a story, starting of an incident or an event, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given question,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A &lt;/strong&gt;is the first sentence and &lt;strong&gt;sentence F&lt;/strong&gt; is the last one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We have to &lt;strong&gt;rearrange the&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;rest&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentences accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Absulum, the reindeer elf worked in the reindeer barn.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;This sentence tells us that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Absulum&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is an elf who worked in the reindeer &lt;strong&gt;barn&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Absulum&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; had to clean&amp;nbsp;this reindeer &lt;strong&gt;barn&lt;/strong&gt; (a large farm building used for storing grain, hay, or straw or for housing livestock). Hence, &lt;strong&gt;Sentence&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;will be the next one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As he had to clean this &lt;strong&gt;barn&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;every day, it was a very dirty job. Hence, &lt;strong&gt;Sentence E&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence because &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Absulum&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; kept&amp;nbsp;the reindeer well-groomed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence because it is connected with &lt;strong&gt;Sentence B&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;because it tells what he did to keep the&amp;nbsp;reindeer well-groomed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Absulum, the reindeer elf worked in the reindeer barn.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;He had to clean it every day, and that was hard work.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;It was such a dirty job to mop, slop, scour and scrape every corner.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;He also had to keep the reindeer well-groomed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;He had to give them all a bath and brush their fur.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;F&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;He worked his fingers to the bone, but it seemed that no one cared.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Absulum, the reindeer elf worked in the reindeer barn.&amp;nbsp;He had to clean it every day, and that was hard work.&amp;nbsp;It was such a dirty job to mop, slop, scour and scrape every corner.&amp;nbsp;He also had to keep the reindeer well-groomed.&amp;nbsp;He had to give them all a bath and brush their fur.&amp;nbsp;He worked his fingers to the bone, but it seemed that no one cared.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;intensify&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Aggravate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;to make something worse or more serious. (स्थिति को) बिगाड़ देना; बदतर करना या होना, अधिक गंभीर बनाना&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; synonyms &lt;/span&gt;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Aggravate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;annoy, bother, bug, burn (up), chafe, eat, exasperate, frost, gall, get, grate, gripe, hack (off), irk, irritate, itch, nark, nettle, peeve, intensify, persecute, pique, put out, rasp, rile, ruffle, spite, vex&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; the &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonym&lt;/span&gt; of the given word, we can say that the word &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Intensify&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; is the &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;most similar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;Intensify&amp;#39; &lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;to become or to make something greater or stronger. (तीव्रतर, प्रबल या उग्रतर हो जाना या कर देना)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;. Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; meaning&lt;/span&gt; of other given options:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color:  (255, 255, 255); width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Words&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Influence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;the power to affect, change or control somebody/something.&lt;br /&gt;
			(व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या वस्&amp;zwj;तु को प्रभावित, परिवर्तन या नियंत्रित करने की शक्ति)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Illustrate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to explain or make something clear by using examples, pictures, or diagrams.&lt;br /&gt;
			(उदाहरणों, चित्रों या आरेखों की सहायता से किसी बात को समझना या स्&amp;zwj;पष्&amp;zwj;ट करना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Illuminate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to shine a light on something or to decorate something with lights.&lt;br /&gt;
			(किसी वस्&amp;zwj;तु को प्रकाश से आलोकित करना या बत्तियों से सजाना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt; of the word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;Aggravate&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; are &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;calm, conciliate&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example &lt;/span&gt;of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;Aggravate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;/span&gt;in a&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt; sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;She &lt;strong&gt;aggravated&lt;/strong&gt; an old knee injury.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;when he has plan&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;when he had planned&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;when he has plan&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence has &lt;strong&gt;two errors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;First, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;has&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;had&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;plan&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;planned&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;When two actions occur in the past, one after the other, the first action is expressed in Past perfect tense and the second action is expressed in Simple past tense&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For Examples:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The patient &lt;strong&gt;had died &lt;/strong&gt;before the doctor &lt;strong&gt;came&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He &lt;strong&gt;came &lt;/strong&gt;after she &lt;strong&gt;had gone&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is so because the sentence is in the past tense. The action of Dhruv planning to settle the dues happened before the person asked him.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the action of him asking Dhruv will be expressed in &lt;strong&gt;simple past tense&lt;/strong&gt; and the action of Dhruv planning to settle the dues will be expressed in the &lt;strong&gt;past perfect tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I asked Dhruv &lt;strong&gt;when he had planned&lt;/strong&gt; to settle the dues.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;when he has plan&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के बजाय &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;when he had planned&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का उपयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में दो errors हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;जब दो क्रियाएं अतीत में होती हैं, तो एक के बाद एक, पहली क्रिया को Past perfect tense में और दूसरी क्रिया को Simple past tense में व्यक्त किया जाता है।&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;उदाहरण के लिए:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The patient &lt;strong&gt;had died&lt;/strong&gt; before the doctor &lt;strong&gt;came&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He &lt;strong&gt;came &lt;/strong&gt;after she&lt;strong&gt; had gone&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ऐसा इसलिए है क्योंकि वाक्य भूतकाल में है। ध्रुव की बकाया राशि का निपटान करने की योजना की कार्रवाई उस व्यक्ति के पूछने से पहले ही हो गई।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार, ध्रुव से पूछने की उसकी क्रिया &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;simple past tense&lt;/span&gt; में व्यक्त की जाएगी और ध्रुव की बकाया राशि का निपटान करने की योजना को &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;past perfect tense&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;में व्यक्त किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;पहले&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;has&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;had&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में और&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;plan&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;planned&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3 &lt;/strong&gt;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;It was agreed by them that the elections should be postponed.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The given sentence has&lt;strong&gt; two clauses.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;principle clause&lt;/strong&gt; is followed by a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;noun clause&lt;/strong&gt; as an object, the &lt;strong&gt;passive voice&lt;/strong&gt; is made as follows:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principle clause + conjunction + noun&amp;nbsp;clause. (Active Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It + was/were + verb + by + object + conjunction + noun clause. (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;We hope that Hansa will clear the exam.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;It is hoped that Hansa will clear the exam.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;It was agreed by them that the elections should be postponed.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​दिया गया वाक्य&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Passive Voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में दो उपवाक्य हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;जब &lt;strong&gt;Principle Clause&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के बाद &lt;strong&gt;Noun Clause Object&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के रूप में होता है तो &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; निम्नानुसार बनाई जाती है:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principle clause + conjunction + noun clause. (Active Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It +was/were + verb + by + object + conjunction + noun clause. (Passive Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;We hope that Hansa will clear the exam.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;It is hoped that Hansa will clear the exam.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Transformation of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Infinitives&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Structure of it is&amp;nbsp;as follows
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject(Objective case) + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + object(subjective case).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your child is to learn chess. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Chess is to be learnt by your child. (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;replied to my letter&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It should be improved from &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;replied mine letter&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;replied to my letter&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;my&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used in place of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;mine&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;possessive adjectives&lt;/strong&gt; are used to show ownership of an item or an idea.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the use of the possessive pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;mine&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Possessive pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; include those used as &lt;strong&gt;adjectives&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;my, your, his, her, its, our, their, and whose&lt;/strong&gt;) and those that take the place of nouns (&lt;strong&gt;mine, yours, his, hers, ours, and theirs&lt;/strong&gt;). Note that possessive pronouns do not use an apostrophe to indicate a possessive form.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;After the verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;replied&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; the preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used because&amp;nbsp;the verb &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;respond&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; requires a prepositional phrase if in the sentence, for one reason or another, it becomes necessary to explain &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to whom&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot; Hence, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He replied to my letter after a month.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसे&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;replied mine letter&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;से&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;replied to my letter&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;कर दिया जाए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;mine&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;my&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए क्योंकि किसी वस्तु या विचार के स्वामित्व को दर्शाने के लिए &lt;strong&gt;possessive adjectives &lt;/strong&gt;का प्रयोग किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;अत: &lt;strong&gt;possessive pronoun&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;mine&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का प्रयोग गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Possessive Pronous&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में वे शामिल होते हैं जो &lt;strong&gt;adjective&lt;/strong&gt; के रूप में उपयोग किए जाते हैं (&lt;strong&gt;my, your, his, her, its, our, their, and whose&lt;/strong&gt;) और वे जो संज्ञाओं (&lt;strong&gt;mine, yours, his, hers, ours, and theirs&lt;/strong&gt;) का स्थान लेते हैं। ध्यान दें कि स्वामित्व वाले सर्वनाम एक स्वत्वबोधक रूप को इंगित करने के लिए एक एस्ट्रोफ़े का उपयोग नहीं करते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Verb &amp;#39;replied&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;के बाद&lt;strong&gt; preposition &amp;#39;to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का उपयोग किया जाना चाहिए क्योंकि क्रिया &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;respond&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; के लिए एक &lt;strong&gt;prepositional phrase&lt;/strong&gt; की आवश्यकता होती है यदि वाक्य में, एक कारण या किसी अन्य के लिए, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;to whom&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; समझाना आवश्यक हो जाता है। अतः &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 2&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;complete details&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;ins and outs&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;complete details&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ins and outs:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the detailed or complicated facts of something. (पूरा विवरण)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: I know how to use computers, but I don&amp;#39;t really understand the &lt;strong&gt;ins and outs &lt;/strong&gt;of how they work.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;s&gt;The given sentence talks about the person who knows complete details of the case and has been chosen to defend the accused (&lt;strong&gt;a person who is on trial in a law court).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/s&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;C&lt;/em&gt;&lt;i&gt;omplete details&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning and examples of some&amp;nbsp;idioms of the word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Play&amp;#39;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(0, 204, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Idiom&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(0, 204, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(0, 204, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;play (merry) hell with sth&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to seriously damage or confuse something&lt;/td&gt;
