&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used instead of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A word family is a group of words that are derived from a&lt;strong&gt; common stem&lt;/strong&gt;, such as &lt;em&gt;choose, choice, chosen, and choosable.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Words in a family may belong to different parts of speech, but they usually have closely related meanings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some families contain multiple words from the same part of speech, such as &lt;em&gt;relation and relationship.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While the meanings of these words may be similar, they are usually not interchangeable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Selecting the right word from the family depends on context.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the examples below:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is a different between love and attachment.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is a difference between love and attachment.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given context a &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; form should be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;a feeling or belief that something is wrong or that somebody has done something wrong.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;She was arrested on &lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt; of murder.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;His loyalty and honesty are above &lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;एक शब्द परिवार शब्दों का एक समूह है जो एक &lt;strong&gt;common stem&lt;/strong&gt; से लिया गया है, जैसे कि &lt;em&gt;choose, choice, chosen, and choosable.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;एक परिवार में शब्द भाषण के विभिन्न भागों से संबंधित हो सकते हैं, लेकिन आमतौर पर उनके निकट से संबंधित अर्थ होते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;कुछ परिवारों में भाषण के एक ही हिस्से से कई शब्द होते हैं, जैसे &lt;em&gt;relation and relationship.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;जबकि इन शब्दों के अर्थ समान हो सकते हैं, वे आमतौर पर विनिमेय नहीं होते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवार से सही शब्द का चुनाव संदर्भ पर निर्भर करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;आइए नीचे दिए गए उदाहरण देखें:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is a &lt;strong&gt;different&lt;/strong&gt; between love and attachment.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is a &lt;strong&gt;difference&lt;/strong&gt; between love and attachment.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए संदर्भ में एक &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; रूप का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Suspicion&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; शब्द का अर्थ है &amp;#39;ऐसी भावना या विश्वास कि कुछ गलत है या किसी ने कुछ गलत किया है; संदेह, शक; यह धारणा कि दाल में कुछ काला है&amp;#39;।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;She was arrested on &lt;strong&gt;suspicion&lt;/strong&gt; of murder.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;BADC&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting off a story, starting of an incident or an event, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the given question is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the starting of a story.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;The author tells us that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Prashant&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; had gone to &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ersama&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; which is located in &lt;strong&gt;Odisha&lt;/strong&gt; to meet his friend.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it tells us about the weather of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ersama&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; when he was there.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it further explains how the storm-ravaged the situation there.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;: Prashant had gone to Ersama, a coastal town in Odisha, to spend the day with a friend.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Suddenly in the evening, a dark and menacing storm quickly gathered.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Winds beat against the houses with a fury never witnessed before.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;The destruction wrought by the storm continued for the next 36 hours, although the wind speed reduced.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Prashant had gone to Ersama, a coastal town in Odisha, to spend the day with a friend. Suddenly in the evening, a dark and menacing storm quickly gathered. Winds beat against the houses with a fury never witnessed before. The destruction wrought by the storm continued for the next 36 hours, although the wind speed reduced.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;ACBEDF&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting off a story, starting of an incident or an event, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given question, sentence&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the first sentence. And&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sentence F&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the last one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We have to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rearrange the&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentences accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Suddenly I noticed smoke pouring in through the seams of the ceiling.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;this is the starting of an incident.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; tells us that the author noticed the smoke coming from the ceiling. After it, &lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; should be used because it expresses&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;how smoke&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; began to fill the room.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;After seeing the smoke in the room, the author ran out of the room to the front&amp;nbsp;yard. Hence, &lt;strong&gt;Sentence B &lt;/strong&gt;should be the next one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence E&lt;/strong&gt; should be the next one because it tells us how the roof&amp;nbsp;got engulfed in flames as soon as they ran out into the front yard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Next, &lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; should be used next because &lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; tells us about what the author did after reaching the front yard i.e. he ran&amp;nbsp;to the neighbours to call the fire department.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Suddenly I noticed smoke pouring in through the seams of the ceiling.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;The smoke began to fill the room so quickly that we could barely see.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Groping our way to the front door we all ran out into the front yard.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;By the time we made our way outside, the whole roof was engulfed in flames.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I ran to the neighbours to call the fire department.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I saw mother run back into the house and I screamed, &amp;ldquo;Mom! No!&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Suddenly I noticed smoke pouring in through the seams of the ceiling. The smoke began to fill the room so quickly that we could barely see. Groping our way to the front door we all ran out into the front yard. By the time we made our way outside, the whole roof was engulfed in flames. I ran to the neighbours to call the fire department.&amp;nbsp;I saw mother run back into the house and I screamed, &amp;ldquo;Mom! No!&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The matter has been discussed by the committee for several days.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question, we have to change it into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Passive Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + has/have + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + has/have + been + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + Object (Subjective&amp;nbsp; Case). (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;We &lt;strong&gt;have finalized &lt;/strong&gt;the site for our new factory. (Active Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The site for our new factory &lt;strong&gt;has been finalized&lt;/strong&gt; by us. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject of the given sentence is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;The committee&amp;#39; a&lt;/span&gt;nd the object of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;the matter&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be put in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be put in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the subject.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;has discussed&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;has been discussed&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The matter has been discussed by the committee for several days.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Active Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + has/have + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case)+ has/have + been + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + Object (Subjective Case). (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;We &lt;strong&gt;have finalized &lt;/strong&gt;the site for our new factory. (Active Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The site for our new factory&lt;strong&gt; has been finalized&lt;/strong&gt; by us. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;subject&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;The committee&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; है और दिए गए वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;object&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;the matter&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;रखा जाएगा और &lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt; रखी जाएगी।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;और &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has discussed&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has been discussed&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;descrete&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given options &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;descrete&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is an incorrectly spelt word.&amp;nbsp;Its&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;spelling is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Discrete&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at its meaning:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Discrete&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;individually separate and distinct. (व्यक्तिगत रूप से अलग और विशिष्ट)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Speech sounds are produced as a continuous sound signal rather than &lt;strong&gt;discrete&lt;/strong&gt; units.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words given in the other options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width: 50px; height: 20px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width: 150px; height: 20px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Ascertain&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to find something out.&lt;br /&gt;
			(कुछ पता लगाना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Inherit&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to receive property, money, etc. from somebody who has died.&lt;br /&gt;
			(मृतक की संपत्ति, धन आदि को (उत्तराधिकार या विरासत के रूप में) प्राप्&amp;zwj;त करना)&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Glorify&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to make somebody/something appear better or more important than he/she/it really is.&lt;br /&gt;
			(बढ़ा-चढ़ाकर कहना)&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;whom&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given fill-in-the-blank the most appropriate answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;whom&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Whom&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;used instead of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;who&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;as the object of a verb or preposition. (&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Whom&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; preposition या verb के object के रूप में&lt;strong&gt; &amp;lsquo;who&amp;rsquo; &lt;/strong&gt;के स्&amp;zwj;थान पर प्रयुक्त होता&amp;nbsp;है)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;I met a man with &lt;strong&gt;whom&lt;/strong&gt; I used to work.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I have nobody &lt;strong&gt;whom &lt;/strong&gt;I can confide in.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meanings &lt;/strong&gt;of other words given in the options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Which&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;used to add extra information to a previous clause, in writing usually after a comma. (आमतौर पर अल्पविराम के बाद लिखित रूप में, पिछले खंड में अतिरिक्त जानकारी जोड़ने के लिए उपयोग किया जाता है)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;used especially in questions when asking about which person owns or is responsible for something. (विशेष रूप से प्रश्नों में उपयोग किया जाता है जब यह पूछा जाता है कि कौन सा व्यक्ति किसी चीज का मालिक है या उसके लिए जिम्मेदार है)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whoever&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;any person who;&amp;nbsp;used in questions as a way of expressing surprise. (कोई भी व्यक्ति जो; प्रश्नों में आश्चर्य व्यक्त करने के तरीके के रूप में उपयोग किया जाता है)&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;She said to me, &amp;ldquo;I gave your message to your mother.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/strong&gt; As per the question we have to change it into &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;told&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;because in the given sentence reporting Verb&amp;nbsp;has an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;object&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;My&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;your&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because in &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;direct to indirect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; transformation &lt;strong&gt;second-person&lt;/strong&gt; pronouns are changed according to the subject of the object of the reporting verb.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;she&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because we know that it&amp;nbsp;changes according to the subject of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the reporting verb.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here, the subject of the reporting verb is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;She&amp;#39;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The past perfect tense&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Had given&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is changed to simple past tense &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;gave&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Because we know that the given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the past perfect tense and &amp;#39;Had + V&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; is changed into &amp;#39;V&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;(past perfect tense changes to simple past tense).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She said to me, &amp;ldquo;I gave your message to your mother.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Told&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि दिए गए वाक्य में रिपोर्टिंग वर्ब में &amp;#39;ऑब्जेक्ट&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;My&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;your&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;direct to indirect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; परिवर्तन में &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; के &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; के अनुसार दूसरे व्यक्ति के &lt;strong&gt;pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; बदल दिए जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;she&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि हम जानते हैं कि यह &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; के &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; के अनुसार बदलता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यहाँ, &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का विषय &amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;she&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;had given&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;gave&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;क्योंकि हम जानते हैं कि दिया गया वाक्य &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;past perfect tense&lt;/span&gt; ​​में है और&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Had + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;V&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;में बदल दिया गया है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;According to me&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;according to me&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;accordingly to my opinion&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Accordingly&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is an &lt;strong&gt;adverb&lt;/strong&gt;, and never begins a sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;in this way, following rules.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The boss told me how to do the project, and I acted &lt;strong&gt;accordingly&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;According to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;following; in a way that agrees with&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (similar meaning to accordingly) but it can begin a sentence and is usually followed by a noun or a noun phrase.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;According&lt;/strong&gt; to the memo we have just received, all employees must now park in the company&amp;#39;s parking lot.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We usually use an &lt;strong&gt;objective pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; after a &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt;, which serves as the &lt;strong&gt;object of a preposition or the object of a verb&lt;/strong&gt; or a sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; are those pronouns that receive the action in a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They are &lt;strong&gt;me, you, him, her, us, them, and whom&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Any noun receiving action in the sentence, like these pronouns, is an object and is categorized as an objective case.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, in the given sentence &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;me&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used instead of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;my&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;According to me&lt;/strong&gt; your essay is the best.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;accordingly to my opinion&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;according to me&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Accordingly&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; एक &lt;strong&gt;adverb&lt;/strong&gt; है, और कभी भी एक वाक्य शुरू नहीं करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसका अर्थ है &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;इस तरह;&amp;nbsp;नियमों का पालन करना।&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: The boss told me how to do the project, and I acted &lt;strong&gt;accordingly&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;According to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का अर्थ है &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;निम्नलिखित; के अनुसार&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (इसका वही अर्थ है जो &amp;#39;accordingly&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;का&amp;nbsp;है) लेकिन यह एक वाक्य शुरू कर सकता है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: &lt;strong&gt;According&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt; the memo we have just received, all employees must now park in the company&amp;#39;s parking lot.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हम आमतौर पर एक &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt; के बाद एक &lt;strong&gt;obejctive pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; का उपयोग करते हैं, जो &lt;strong&gt;object of a preposition &lt;/strong&gt;या&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;object of a verb&lt;/strong&gt; के रूप में कार्य करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Object pronouns&lt;/span&gt; वे सर्वनाम होते हैं जो एक वाक्य में क्रिया प्राप्त करते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;वे &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;me, you, him, her, us, them,&lt;/span&gt; और &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;whom&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इन सर्वनामों की तरह, वाक्य में क्रिया प्राप्त करने वाली कोई भी संज्ञा एक object है और इसे एक objective case के रूप में वर्गीकृत किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;अतः दिए गए वाक्य में &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;my&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;me&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग होना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;BDCA&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting of an incident, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the given question is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the starting of an incident.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It talks about the author flying to England for a week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it tells about the events that happened when the author was checking in at the airport.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it is connected with &lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; and further tells that the author had kept&amp;nbsp;the frequent flyer card in the carry-on bag hanging around his neck.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly, &lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;entence &lt;/strong&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used because it tells about the bag&amp;#39;s zip getting jammed, and the author couldn&amp;#39;t open it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;: We were flying to England for a week.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;As we were checking in, I remembered that I was a member of the frequent flyer programme.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I also remembered that I had put the frequent flyer card in the carry-on bag hanging around my neck.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;The zip on the bag got jammed and wouldn&amp;rsquo;t open no matter how hard I pulled at it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;We were flying to England for a week.&amp;nbsp;As we were checking in, I remembered that I was a member of the frequent flyer programme.&amp;nbsp;I also remembered that I had put the frequent flyer card in the carry-on bag hanging around my neck.&amp;nbsp;The zip on the bag got jammed and wouldn&amp;rsquo;t open no matter how hard I pulled at it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;I was not ridiculing anybody.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change the sentence into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Form.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;past continuous tense&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of these kinds of sentences is:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + was/were + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ ing + Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject(Objective Case) + was/were + being + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + Object (subjective case). (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He was riding a bike.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A bike was being ridden by him.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;was being ridiculed&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;was not ridiculing&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The preposition&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Nobody&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;anybody&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;me&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;(subject).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 1.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I was not ridiculing anybody.&lt;/em&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें वाक्य को &lt;strong&gt;Active Voice&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;past continuous tense&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों की संरचना है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + was/were + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ ing + Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject(Objective Case) + was/were + being + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + Object (subjective case). (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;उदाहरण:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He was riding a bike.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A bike was being ridden by him.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ दिए गए वाक्य में &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;was being ridiculed&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;was not ridiculing&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; हटा दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;me&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; (subject) में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Nobody&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;anybody&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Transformation of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Infinitives:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (objective case) + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + object (Subjective case). (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The teacher is to solve the doubt of every student.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The doubt of every student is to be solved by the teacher.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Anu said, &amp;ldquo;I want to see if I can do a back-flip.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct&amp;nbsp;Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/strong&gt; will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;She&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because in &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;direct to indirect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; transformation the first-person pronouns are changed according to the subject of the reporting verb.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Wanted&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;want&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;could&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;can&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Anu said, &amp;quot;I want to see if I can do a back-flip&amp;quot;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य इनडायरेक्ट स्पीच में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे डायरेक्ट स्पीच में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;She&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;direct to indirect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; परिवर्तन में &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; के &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; के अनुसार पहले व्यक्ति के &lt;strong&gt;pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; बदल दिए जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Wanted&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;want&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Could&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;can&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 2 &lt;/strong&gt;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;We object to this unfair proposal.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + is/am/are + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object (Subjective Case). (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Aastha teaches English.&amp;nbsp;(Active Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;English is taught by Aastha.&amp;nbsp;(Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;This unfair proposal&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;us&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be put in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be put in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;is objected to&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;object to&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;We object to this unfair proposal.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice में बदलना होगा।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + is/am/are + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object (Subjective Case). (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Aastha teaches English.&amp;nbsp;(Active Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;English is taught by Aastha.&amp;nbsp;(Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;This unfair proposal&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;object &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;us&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt; रखा जाएगा और &lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;रखी जाएगी।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;is object to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;object to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&lt;strong&gt; विकल्प 2&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The teacher said to the students, &amp;ldquo;Can you prepare for the debate by next week?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;asked&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/strong&gt; will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;if&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;We know that &lt;strong&gt;second-person pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; are changed according to the &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; (the students)&amp;nbsp;of the &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Could&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;can&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The adverb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;the following week&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;next week&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The teacher said to the students, &amp;ldquo;Can you prepare for the debate by next week?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&lt;strong&gt; Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यहां, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;asked&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;संयोजन &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;if&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; हटा दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;हम जानते हैं कि&lt;strong&gt; reporting verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;की वस्तु (the students) के अनुसार &lt;strong&gt;second person pronouns &lt;/strong&gt;में&amp;nbsp;बदल जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;could&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;can&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adverb &amp;#39;the following week&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;next week&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;set free&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;set free&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;set at freedom&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;set free&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is an &lt;strong&gt;idiomatic&lt;/strong&gt; expression.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set free (from something):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;To liberate someone or something from imprisonment or confinement. (किसी को या किसी चीज को कारावास से मुक्त करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The activists snuck into the lab and &lt;strong&gt;set free&lt;/strong&gt; nearly 200 animals being used for biological experiments.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The prisoner was &lt;strong&gt;set free&lt;/strong&gt; early.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;and&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given fill-in-the-blank the most appropriate answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;and&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;both&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is followed by &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;both...and&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; to emphasize the link between two things.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: &lt;strong&gt;Both&lt;/strong&gt; Britain &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt; France agree on the treaty.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He is both diligent &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt; efficient.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ, दिए गए रिक्त स्थान की पूर्ति में सबसे उपयुक्त उत्तर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हम जानते हैं कि &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;both&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के बाद &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; आता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हम दो चीजों के बीच की कड़ी पर जोर देने के लिए &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;both ... and&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; का उपयोग करते हैं।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: &lt;strong&gt;Both&lt;/strong&gt; Britain &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt; France agree on the treaty.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Hardly/Scarcely&amp;#39; is followed by &amp;#39;when&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:​&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hardly&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;did I see him&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;when&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;I stopped my car.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;BDAC&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting of an incident, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the given question is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the starting of an incident.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It tells us that Nancy&amp;#39;s uncle gifted her a bubble shooter on her birthday.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it is connected with &lt;strong&gt;Sentence B.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it tells us about the different types of bubbles and their respective sizes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used because it tells how Nancy played&amp;nbsp;with those bubbles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;: Nancy&amp;rsquo;s uncle gifted her a bubble shooter for her birthday.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Now, Nancy could blow bubbles of all sizes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Some were big and floated around while others were small and popped immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;She chased them around, trying to hold them in her hands.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Nancy&amp;rsquo;s uncle gifted her a bubble shooter for her birthday.&amp;nbsp;Now, Nancy could blow bubbles of all sizes. Some were big and floated around while others were small and popped immediately.&amp;nbsp;She chased them around, trying to hold them in her hands.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;denied taking&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;denied taking&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;denied to take&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt; is formed from &lt;strong&gt;a verb&lt;/strong&gt;, always ends in&lt;strong&gt; -ing, &lt;/strong&gt;and always acts as &lt;strong&gt;a noun.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When following a &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt;, a &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;gerund phrase&lt;/strong&gt; is the object of the verb, &lt;strong&gt;a subject complement, or the subject of an inverted sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Certain verbs are almost always followed by a &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt;. Unfortunately, there is no easy way to remember what those &lt;strong&gt;verbs&lt;/strong&gt; are.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at some &lt;strong&gt;verbs&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Begin, start, love, like, hate, stop, finish, enjoy, prefer, fear, remember, forget, mind, miss,&amp;nbsp;suggest, practice, understand, keep, admit, &lt;strong&gt;deny&lt;/strong&gt;, detest, rest, defer, worth, risk, regret, consider.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;She started&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;singing&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the gerund&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;taking&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;will be used in place of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to take&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The porter &lt;strong&gt;denied taking&lt;/strong&gt; the money.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;denied to take&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;denied taking&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;एक &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;gerund&lt;/span&gt; एक &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; से बनता है, हमेशा -&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ing&lt;/span&gt; में समाप्त होता है, और हमेशा एक &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; के रूप में कार्य करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;एक &lt;strong&gt;Verb&lt;/strong&gt; का पालन करते समय, एक &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt; या &lt;strong&gt;gerund phrase&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; का &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; है, एक &lt;strong&gt;subject complement,&lt;/strong&gt; या एक उल्टे वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;कुछ क्रियाओं का लगभग हमेशा एक &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt; द्वारा पालन किया जाता है। दुर्भाग्य से, उन क्रियाओं को याद रखने का कोई आसान तरीका नहीं है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;आइए कुछ क्रियाओं को देखें:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Begin, start, love, like, hate, stop, finish, enjoy, prefer, fear, remember, forget, mind, miss,&amp;nbsp;suggest, practice, understand, keep, admit, deny, detest, rest, defer, worth, risk, regret, consider.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;She started&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;singing&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to take&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर gerund &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;taking&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का उपयोग किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 2&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to correct a mistake&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate meaning of the given idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;To make amends&amp;#39; &lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;to correct a mistake&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To make amends:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to do something to correct a mistake that one has made or a bad situation that one has caused. (किसी गलती को सुधारने के लिए कुछ करने के लिए जो किसी ने की है या एक बुरी स्थिति जो किसी के कारण हुई है)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;She tried &lt;strong&gt;to make amends&lt;/strong&gt; by apologizing to him.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;To correct a mistake.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at some idioms&amp;nbsp;the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Get&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Idiom&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Get socked with something&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to suddenly receive something that causes you problems. (अचानक कुछ ऐसा प्राप्त करना जिससे आपको परेशानी हो)&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you don&amp;#39;t pay your credit card bill on time, you&amp;#39;ll&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;get socked with a huge&amp;nbsp;late fee.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Get someone&amp;#39;s wires crossed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to have a different understanding of the same situation. (एक ही स्थिति की एक अलग समझ रखने के लिए)&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;We must have&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;got our wires crossed&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; I thought she was arriving tomorrow, not today.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Get something out of your system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;to do something enough so that you do not want to do it any longer. (इतना कुछ करने के लिए कि आप इसे अब और नहीं करना चाहते हैं)&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let the kids run around a little longer, maybe they&amp;rsquo;ll&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;get it out of their system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;She said to me, &amp;ldquo;How tall you have grown!&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct&amp;nbsp;Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of an &lt;strong&gt;Exclamatory Sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The notion of these kinds of sentences is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;joy, sorrow, surprise, applause, detest, hate, etc.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reporting Verbs are changed according to the notion of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Reported Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;These&amp;nbsp;verbs are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;exclaimed&amp;nbsp;with surprise, exclaimed with sorrow, exclaimed with joy, exclaimed with contempt, etc.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Exclamatory words&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Ah!, Ha!, My God!, Oh!, Alas!, Bravo!&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are removed in Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;That&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Inverted commas&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Tense, Pronoun, and Adverbials&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are changed according to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nitin said, &amp;quot;What a match it was!&amp;quot;. (Direct Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nitin exclaimed that it was a good match. (Indirect Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;exclaimed&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/strong&gt; will be added.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;had grown&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;have grown&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;. (past perfect tense changes into present perfect tense)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She said to me, &amp;quot;How tall you have grown!&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/mistake-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mistake Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We tend to go for &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; but it would be wrong because the given sentence is an example of an &lt;strong&gt;exclamatory sentence&lt;/strong&gt;. And &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is an example of an &lt;strong&gt;assertive sentence&lt;/strong&gt;. (हम विकल्प 2 के लिए जाते हैं लेकिन यह गलत होगा क्योंकि दिया गया वाक्य&lt;strong&gt; exclamatory sentence&lt;/strong&gt; का एक उदाहरण है। और &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 2 &lt;/strong&gt;एक &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentence&lt;/span&gt; का एक उदाहरण है।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; Option 4&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे&lt;strong&gt; Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Exclamatory Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों की धारणा &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;joy, sorrow, surprise, applause, detest, hate, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reported Speech&lt;/strong&gt; की धारणा के अनुसार &lt;strong&gt;Reporting Verbs&lt;/strong&gt; को बदल दिया जाता है। ये क्रियाएँ हैं: &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exclaimed&amp;nbsp;with surprise, exclaimed with sorrow, exclaimed with joy, exclaimed with contempt, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;विस्मयादिबोधक शब्द &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Ah!, Ha!, My God!, Oh!, Alas!, Bravo!&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt; में हटा दिया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;That&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Tense, Pronoun, and Adverbials&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentences&lt;/span&gt; के अनुसार बदले जाते हैं।
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;उदाहरण:&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nitin said, &amp;quot;What a match it was!&amp;quot;. (Direct Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nitin exclaimed that it was a good match. (Indirect Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;exclaimed&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा। &lt;strong&gt;Direct&lt;/strong&gt; रूप से &lt;strong&gt;Indirect&lt;/strong&gt; परिवर्तन में सर्वनाम के दूसरे रूप को रिपोर्टिंग क्रिया की &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के अनुसार बदल दिया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;had grown&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;have grown&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&lt;strong&gt; विकल्प 4&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;ADBECF&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting off a story, starting of an incident or an event, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given question, &lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;entence &lt;/strong&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the first sentence and &lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;entence &lt;/strong&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the last one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We have to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rearrange&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentences accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Santosh&amp;rsquo;s parents were affluent landowners who could afford to send their children to the best schools.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;This sentence tells us that &lt;strong&gt;Santosh&amp;#39;s&lt;/strong&gt; parents were rich landowners so they could send their children to the best schools.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence because it is connected with &lt;strong&gt;Sentence A.&lt;/strong&gt; As per &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Sentence&amp;nbsp;A&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Santosh&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; belonged to a rich family, still, she went to the local village school.&amp;nbsp;Hence, both are connected.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it tells what step Santosh took to fight the custom of her family, i.e. to study in the local village school.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because the right moment for which Santosh had been waiting came at the age of sixteen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence because it tells us that most of the village girls used to get married at the age of sixteen. She didn&amp;#39;t want to get married at that&amp;nbsp;age and therefore, this was the moment she was waiting for.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Santosh&amp;rsquo;s parents were affluent landowners who could afford to send their children to the best schools.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;But in line with the custom of the family, Santosh was sent to the local village school.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;So, she decided to fight the matter in her own quiet way when the right moment arrived.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;And, the right moment came when she turned sixteen.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At sixteen, most of the girls in her village used to get married.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;But a marriage at that age was the last thing on Santosh&amp;rsquo;s mind.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Santosh&amp;rsquo;s parents were affluent landowners who could afford to send their children to the best schools.&amp;nbsp;But in line with the custom of the family, Santosh was sent to the local village school.&amp;nbsp;So, she decided to fight the matter in her own quiet way when the right moment arrived.&amp;nbsp;And, the right moment came when she turned sixteen.&amp;nbsp; At sixteen, most of the girls in her village used to get married.&amp;nbsp;But a marriage at that age was the last thing on Santosh&amp;rsquo;s mind.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Prologue&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate word for the given group of words is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Prologue&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Prologue&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a piece of writing or a speech that introduces a play, poem, etc. (नाटक, कविता आदि को प्रस्&amp;zwj;तुत करने वाला लेख या भाषण; प्रस्&amp;zwj;तावना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The &lt;strong&gt;prologue&lt;/strong&gt; to the novel is written in the form of a newspaper account.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Prologue&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words given in the options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dialogue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;conversation between people in a book, play, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
			(नाटक आदि में संवाद, लोगों के बीच वार्तालाप)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Epilogue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;a short piece that is added at the end of a book, play, etc., and that comments on what has gone before.&lt;br /&gt;
			(किसी पुस्&amp;zwj;तक, नाटक आदि का अंतवचन, उपसंहार, भरत वाक्&amp;zwj;य)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monologue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;a long speech by one person, for example in a play.&lt;br /&gt;
			(अकेले व्यक्ति का लंबा भाषण (जैसे नाटक में), एकालाप; स्&amp;zwj;वगत भाषण)&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to this rule&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to this rule&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;with these rule&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;exception&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is followed by the preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;To strongly disagree with or take offense at something&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt; (किसी बात पर दृढ़ता से असहमत होना या अपराध करना).&amp;#39;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;I know she takes &lt;strong&gt;exception to&lt;/strong&gt; the way the newspaper represented the data from her study.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;these&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;this&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;these&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; refers to &lt;strong&gt;plural nouns. (here, the noun is singular i.e. rule)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;There is no exception &lt;strong&gt;to this rule.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;so then they can get&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;so that they can get&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;so then they can get&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;So&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is followed by &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; when it answers the question &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;why&lt;/strong&gt;?&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given context,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;so that&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;in order to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use it to begin adverb clauses of purpose.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: It helps to lower blood sugar &lt;strong&gt;so that&lt;/strong&gt; you feel less hungry.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adverb clause is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;so that you feel less hungry.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It shows the &lt;strong&gt;purpose&lt;/strong&gt; of the action in the main clause.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The farmers are using HYV seeds so &lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt; they can get a better yield.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;so then they can get&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;so that they can get&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;So&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के बाद &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; आता है जब यह &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;why?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;question&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उत्तर देता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए संदर्भ में &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;so that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का अर्थ है &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;in order to&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हम इसका उपयोग adverb clauses&amp;nbsp;of purpose को&amp;nbsp;शुरू करने के लिए करते हैं।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: It helps to lower blood sugar&lt;strong&gt; so that &lt;/strong&gt;you feel less hungry.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adverb clauses&amp;nbsp;of purpose है &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;so that you feel less hungry&amp;quot;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यह मुख्य खंड में action के purpose को दर्शाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 2 &lt;/strong&gt;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The little girl said, &amp;ldquo;These butterflies are very colourful.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question, we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct&amp;nbsp;Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will not change because the reporting verb does not have an &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/strong&gt; will be added.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The adverb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;those&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;these&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The auxiliary verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;were&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;are&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The litter girl said, &amp;quot;These butterflies are very colourful.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: 700; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&lt;strong&gt; Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; नहीं बदलेगा क्योंकि &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; में कोई &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; नहीं है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adverb &amp;#39;those&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;these&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;सहायक क्रिया &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;were&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;are&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4 &lt;/strong&gt;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct antonym is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;expand&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Condense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;to become smaller in size or volume through the drawing together of particles of matter.&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;(पदार्थ के कणों के एक साथ आरेखण के माध्यम से आकार या आयतन में छोटा होना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Condense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are &amp;#39;accumulate, grow, increase, inflate, expand&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Expand&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Expand&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;to make greater in size, amount, or number.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(आकार, राशि या संख्या में बड़ा करना)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;. Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of other given options:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(0, 204, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Words&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(0, 204, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Reduce&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to make something less or smaller in quantity, price, size, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
			(मात्रा, क़ीमत, आकार आदि की दृष्टि से घटाना; छोटा करना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Constrict&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to become or make something tighter, narrower, or less.&lt;br /&gt;
			(संकुचित होना या करना; सिकुड़ना, कसना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Repel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;to send or push somebody/something back or away&lt;br /&gt;
			(किसी व्&amp;zwj;यकि्त या वस्&amp;zwj;तु को पीछे या दूर भेज या धकेल देना)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Condense&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;compress, constrict, contract, shrink&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Condense&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in a sentence:&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Over time the once-fluffy material in the pillow had &lt;strong&gt;condensed &lt;/strong&gt;into a lumpy wad.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Administer the medicine every four hours.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Active&amp;nbsp;Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of &lt;strong&gt;imperative sentences.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The transformation of imperative sentences:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If someone gives&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a command, does a&amp;nbsp;request, expresses a desire or wish&amp;nbsp;in sentences then such sentences are called an imperative sentences.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let + subject + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;. (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Teach your students. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let your students be taught. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The medicine&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is the &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;be administered&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;administer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Administer the medicine every four hours.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Active Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Imperative Sentence&lt;/strong&gt; का एक उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imperative Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का परिवर्तन:&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यदि कोई वाक्यों में आदेश देता है,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;एक अनुरोध करता है, एक इच्छा&amp;nbsp;व्यक्त करता है&lt;strong&gt;,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; ऐसे वाक्यों को अनिवार्य वाक्य कहा जाता है।
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let + subject + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;. (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Teach your students. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let your students be taught. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The medicine&amp;#39; subject&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;be administered&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;administer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lost heart&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lost heart&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lost his heart&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Lose&amp;nbsp;heart&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;strong&gt;phrasal verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;that means &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;become discouraged&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As the meaning of the sentence implies a past incident, the past form of &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Lose heart&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt; will be used as&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Lost heart&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to lose all hope or confidence&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(सारा आत्म विश्वास और आशा खो देना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;He told his friend not to&lt;strong&gt; lose heart &lt;/strong&gt;because they might still win the game.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He &lt;strong&gt;lost&amp;nbsp;heart&lt;/strong&gt; because he could not cope with the difficult situation.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;aren&amp;rsquo;t I&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given fill-in-the-blank, the most appropriate option is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;aren&amp;#39;t I&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;positive statement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is followed by a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;question&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;tag whereas, a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;negative statement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is followed by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a positive question tag.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Jack is from Spain,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;isn&amp;#39;t he?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is &lt;strong&gt;positive&lt;/strong&gt;. Hence, it should be followed by&lt;strong&gt; a negative question tag.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The negative question tag of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I am&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;aren&amp;#39;t I&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I am your true friend,&lt;strong&gt; aren&amp;#39;t I?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां, दिए गए रिक्त स्थान की पूर्ति में, सबसे उपयुक्त विकल्प &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;aren&amp;#39;t I&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हम जानते हैं कि एक सकारात्मक कथन के बाद एक नकारात्मक &lt;strong&gt;question tag &lt;/strong&gt;होता है, जबकि एक नकारात्मक कथन के बाद एक सकारात्मक &lt;strong&gt;question tag&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;होता है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Jack is from Spain,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;isn&amp;#39;t he?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य सकारात्मक है। इसलिए, इसके बाद एक नकारात्मक &lt;strong&gt;question tag&lt;/strong&gt; होना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I am&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;का नकारात्मक प्रश्न टैग है &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;aren&amp;#39;t I&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&lt;strong&gt; विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;an young businessman&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;young businessman&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;an young businessman&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here&amp;nbsp;in the given sentence, the indefinite article &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used because&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;young&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;starts with a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;consonant&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sound&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Uranium is &lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt; toxic metal.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;My neighbour is&lt;strong&gt; a young businessman&lt;/strong&gt; who is very friendly with everyone.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;No article is used before&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the possessive case of the proper noun.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Sukhdev&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;bike is blue with an orange seat.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sukhdev&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;bike is blue with an orange seat.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;​​But when there is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a possessive case of a common noun,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;then, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;article&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;can be used before it.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Woman&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Yoga Book.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Woman&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Yoga Book.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;an young businessman&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;young businessman&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ दिए गए वाक्य में, अनिश्चितकालीन &lt;strong&gt;article &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए क्योंकि &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;young&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रारम्भ &lt;strong&gt;consonant sound&lt;/strong&gt; से होता है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: Uranium is &lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt; toxic metal.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;How can your generosity be forgotten by me?&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;active-passive&amp;#39; transformation&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;except for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(who and whom)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;rest of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Wh-family Pronouns&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will remain&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unchanged&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given question&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;How many languages&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will remain unchanged.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Since &lt;strong&gt;modal verb&lt;/strong&gt; has been used in the active voice, therefore, the passive voice will follow the given structure:-
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Active Voice - Modal verb(can) + V1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice - Modal verb(can) + be + V3&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;can forget&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;can&amp;nbsp;be forgotten&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;will be changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;me&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Lastly, the preposition&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;How can your generosity be forgotten by me?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Active Voice&lt;/strong&gt; का उदाहरण है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Active-Passive&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; परिवर्तन में (who और whom) को छोड़कर शेष &lt;strong&gt;Wh&lt;/strong&gt;- परिवार &lt;strong&gt;pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; अपरिवर्तित रहेंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यहां, दिए गए प्रश्न में &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;How many languages&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; अपरिवर्तित रहेंगी।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;चूंकि, Active voice में &lt;strong&gt;modal verb&lt;/strong&gt; का उपयोग किया गया है, इसलिए, passive voice दी गई संरचना का अनुसरण करेगी: -
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Active Voice - Modal verb(can) + V1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice - Modal verb(can) + be + V3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;can forget&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;can be forgotten&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;me&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अंत में, &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; जोड़ा जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;You said that you had scored four goals.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the reporting verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;has&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;no object.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will not be changed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas &lt;/strong&gt;will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be added.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because the &lt;strong&gt;first person pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; are changed according to the &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;V&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;had + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(simple past tense changes into past perfect tense)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;You said that you had scored four goals.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Direct&amp;nbsp;Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य में &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting verb&lt;/span&gt; का कोई &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; नहीं है। इसलिए, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; नहीं बदला जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम हटा दिए जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;संयोजन &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; जोड़ा जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि रिपोर्टिंग क्रिया के विषय के अनुसार पहले व्यक्ति सर्वनाम बदल दिए जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;V&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;had + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;usher&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate word for the given group of words is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;usher&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Usher&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a person who shows people to their seats in a theatre, church, etc. (वह व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति जो थिएटर, चर्च आदि में लोगों को उनका स्&amp;zwj;थान बताता है)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Renan was occupied as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;usher&lt;/strong&gt; only in the evenings.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Usher.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words given in the options:&lt;/li&gt;
