&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;She requested Madhu to post that letter&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Indirect&amp;nbsp;Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;imperative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sentence&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the rules of transformation:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;While changing the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;narration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;of an&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;imperative&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence, we need to follow the given steps:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The notion of the given sentence is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;request&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;The conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; should be used in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a comma (,) and inverted commas (&amp;ldquo; &amp;rdquo;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;requested&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;to&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is followed by&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;V&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;Lastly, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;adverb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;this&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The queen said to his servant, &amp;quot;Cook me some delicious food today.&amp;quot; (Direct Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The queen ordered his servant to cook her some delicious food that day. (Indirect Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;She requested Madhu to post that letter.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Imperative Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;आइए परिवर्तन के नियमों को देखें:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;एक &lt;strong&gt;Imperative Sentence&lt;/strong&gt; का &lt;strong&gt;Narration&lt;/strong&gt; बदलते समय, हमें दिए गए चरणों का पालन करना होगा:&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की धारणा &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;request&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;संयोजन&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;to&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;का प्रयोग अल्पविराम (,) और उल्टे अल्पविराम (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;) के स्थान पर किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;requested&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के बाद &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;V&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; आता है।&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;अंत में, &lt;strong&gt;Adverb &amp;#39;this&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The queen said to his servant, &amp;quot;Cook me some delicious food today.&amp;quot; (Direct Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The queen ordered his servant to cook her some delicious food that day. (Indirect Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 4 &lt;/strong&gt;है।&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;energetic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Languid&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;weak or faint from illness or fatigue;&amp;nbsp;(of a person, manner, or gesture) having or showing a disinclination for physical exertion or effort.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;(बीमारी या थकान से कमजोर या बेहोश;&amp;nbsp;(किसी व्यक्ति, तरीके, या हावभाव का) शारीरिक परिश्रम या प्रयास के प्रति उदासीनता होना या दिखाना&lt;b&gt;)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;b&gt;Languid&lt;/b&gt;&amp;#39; are &amp;#39;ambitious, animated, energetic, enterprising, motivated&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Energetic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Energetic&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;showing or involving great activity or vitality.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(ऊर्जावान)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;. Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of other given options:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Words&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Lethargic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;affected by lethargy; sluggish and apathetic. (सुस्ती से प्रभावित; सुस्त और उदासीन)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Sluggish&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;slow-moving or inactive. (धीमी गति से चलने वाला या निष्क्रिय)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indolent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;wanting to avoid activity or exertion; lazy. (गतिविधि या परिश्रम से बचना चाहते हैं; काम चोर)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Languid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;enervated, lackadaisical, languishing, languorous, limp, listless, spiritless&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Languid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in a sentence:&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A slow, &lt;strong&gt;languid&lt;/strong&gt; smile crossed his features, one that made her body flush and ache for him.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;BCAD&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting of an incident, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the given question is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the starting of an incident.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It talks about the author&amp;nbsp;meeting his grandmother after a long while.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because when the author went to meet his grandmother, he saw her standing at the village bus stand to receive him.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it explains the expressions on the face of the author&amp;#39;s grandmother when he saw her standing&amp;nbsp;at the village bus stand to receive him.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used because it expresses what her grandmother did when she received him.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;: It was quite a long time since I had met my grandmother.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I found her standing at the village bus stand to receive me.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;She looked very excited when she saw me get off the bus.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;She hugged me and tears of joy flowed down her cheeks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;It was quite a long time since I had met my grandmother.&amp;nbsp;I found her standing at the village bus stand to receive me.&amp;nbsp;She looked very excited when she saw me get off the bus.&amp;nbsp;She hugged me and tears of joy flowed down her cheeks.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;He said to you, &amp;ldquo;I will discuss the matter today evening.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct&amp;nbsp;Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given question&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;told&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;speech has an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/strong&gt; will be added.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;he&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; because we know that the first person pronouns are changed according to the subject of the &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;would&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;will&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;. (&lt;strong&gt;Indirect to Direct Transformation&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The adverb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that evening&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;today evening&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He said to you, &amp;ldquo;I will discuss the matter today evening.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यहां, दिए गए प्रश्न में &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;told&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; को &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि &lt;strong&gt;reporting speech&lt;/strong&gt; में एक &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;संयोजन &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; हटा दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;सर्वनाम &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;he&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा। क्योंकि हम जानते हैं कि &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के विषय के अनुसार पहले व्यक्ति &lt;strong&gt;pronoun&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;बदल जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;would&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;will&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा। (अप्रत्यक्ष से प्रत्यक्ष परिवर्तन)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adverb&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that evening&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;today evening&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Pseudonym&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate meaning of the given group of words is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;pseudonym&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Pseudonym&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a name used by somebody, especially a writer, instead of his/her real name. (छद्मनाम, उपनाम; असली नाम के बदले प्रयुक्त, विशेषतः किसी लेखक द्वारा)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;He writes estimable poetry under a &lt;strong&gt;pseudonym&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Pseudonym.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of other words given in the Options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homonym&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;a word that is spelt and pronounced like another word but that has a different meaning.&lt;br /&gt;
			(उच्&amp;zwj;चारण तथा वर्तनी में समान परंतु अर्थ में भिन्&amp;zwj;न शब्&amp;zwj;द; समनाम)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Namesake&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;a person who has the same name as another.&lt;br /&gt;
			(हमनाम, नामराशि; ऐसा व्यक्ति जिसका वही नाम हो जो दूसरे का है)&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alibi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;a statement by somebody that says you were in a different place at the time of a crime and so cannot be guilty of the crime.&lt;br /&gt;
			(अपराध के समय अन्&amp;zwj;यत्र उपस्थित होने का कथन (यह सिद्ध करने के लिए की वह दोषी नहीं है); अन्&amp;zwj;यत्रता)&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The Principal said to Kamal, &amp;ldquo;How is it that you are always late for school?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Asked&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because the given question is an example of an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;interrogative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with a question word.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;is&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;. Because in &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; transformation &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;simple present&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; tense is changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;simple past tense&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;he&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;you&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;because in &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; transformation &lt;strong&gt;second-person pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; is changed according to the &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;How&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used as a conjunction because we know that in an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;interrogative sentence with a question word,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the question word itself is used as a conjunction.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The Principal said to Kamal, &amp;ldquo;How is it that you are always late for school?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है। प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना होगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;asked&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि दिया गया प्रश्न &lt;strong&gt;interrogative sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के साथ एक प्रश्नवाचक वाक्य का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;अल्पविराम और उल्टे अल्पविराम जोड़े जाएंगे।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;is&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;में बदल दिया जाएगा। क्योंकि &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect&amp;#39; transformation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;simple present&amp;#39; tense &lt;/strong&gt;को &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;simple past tense&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; में बदल दिया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;he&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; को&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;you&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;में बदल दिया जाएगा क्योंकि &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect&amp;#39; transformation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;में &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; के &lt;strong&gt;object &lt;/strong&gt;के&amp;nbsp;अनुसार &lt;strong&gt;second person&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के &lt;strong&gt;pronouns&lt;/strong&gt; को बदल दिया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;How&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को एक &lt;strong&gt;conjunction&lt;/strong&gt; के रूप में प्रयोग किया जाएगा क्योंकि हम जानते हैं कि एक &lt;strong&gt;interrogative sentence&lt;/strong&gt; में प्रश्न शब्द का प्रयोग &lt;strong&gt;conjunction&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के रूप में किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;despite of&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;despite&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be used instead of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;despite of&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;despite&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;is never followed by &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We should not say &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;despite of something&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;, say &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;despite something&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Despite&lt;/strong&gt; having very little money, they enjoy life.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;despite&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;without being affected by the thing mentioned.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(के बावजूद)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He could not get a job &lt;strong&gt;despite&lt;/strong&gt; his best efforts.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;despite of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के स्थान पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;despite&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Despite&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; शब्द का कभी भी &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; के साथ प्रयोग नहीं किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;हमें &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;despite of something&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;नहीं कहना चाहिए, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;despite something&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;कहना चाहिए।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: &lt;strong&gt;Despite&lt;/strong&gt; having very little money, they enjoy life.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Despite&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; शब्द का अर्थ है &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;बिना उल्लेख की गई बात से प्रभावित हुए&amp;#39;।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADBECF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting off a story, starting of an incident or an event, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given question,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;entence &lt;/strong&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the first sentence. And &lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;entence &lt;/strong&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the last one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We have to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rearrange&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentences accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the starting of an incident.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; will be the next sentence because it is connected with&lt;strong&gt; Sentence A.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because &lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; tells us that Velu&amp;#39;s legs wobbled and because of this, he sat down on the nearby bench.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence E&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because after sitting down on the bench, he put his small bundle beside him on the bench and looked around.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly, &lt;strong&gt;sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; will be used because when he looked around, he saw a sight that he had never seen in all his eleven years.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;When the train pulled in at Chennai Central, it took Velu some time to get off.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;When he finally stood on the platform, his legs felt wobble.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;So, he sat down on a nearby bench that was unoccupied.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;He put his small bundle beside him on the bench and looked around.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;In all his eleven years he had not seen so many people except at the village fair.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Near him, a group of people sat on their luggage staring at a TV hanging from the roof.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;When the train pulled in at Chennai Central, it took Velu some time to get off.&amp;nbsp;When he finally stood on the platform, his legs felt wobble.&amp;nbsp;So, he sat down on a nearby bench that was unoccupied.&amp;nbsp;He put his small bundle beside him on the bench and looked around.&amp;nbsp;In all his eleven years he had not seen so many people except at the village fair.&amp;nbsp;Near him, a group of people sat on their luggage staring at a TV hanging from the roof.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Don&amp;#39;t feed the animals in the zoo&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + should + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;. (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;an imperative sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If someone gives a command, does request, expresses a desire or wish, suggestion, in sentences then such sentences are called an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;imperative sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The notion of the given sentence is a suggestion.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Help the poor people. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The poor people should be helped. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The subject of the given sentence is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The animals&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Should not be fed&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;should be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Don&amp;#39;t feed&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;Don&amp;#39;t feed the animals in the zoo.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Active Voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Imperative Sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यदि कोई वाक्य में आदेश देता है, अनुरोध करता है, इच्छा व्यक्त करता है, सुझाव देता है, तो ऐसे वाक्यों को&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Imperative Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;कहा जाता है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की धारणा &lt;strong&gt;सुझाव &lt;/strong&gt;है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;V1 + Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + should + be + V3. (Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Help the poor people. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The poor people should be helped. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य का&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The animals&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Should not be fed&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Don&amp;#39;t feed&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;विकल्प 4&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;will never be heard&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;will never be heard&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has never heard&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&lt;strong&gt; passive voice. &lt;/strong&gt;And the&amp;nbsp;notion of the given sentence is &lt;strong&gt;futuristic&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; future tense&lt;/strong&gt; will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;passive verb&lt;/strong&gt; form in the simple future tense is made by putting &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;will/shall + be&lt;/strong&gt; before the &lt;strong&gt;past participle form of the verb.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;I will be helped by her.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;His fine voice &lt;strong&gt;will never be heard&lt;/strong&gt; in this hall again.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहाँ &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has never heard&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;will never be heard&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है&amp;nbsp;और दिए गए वाक्य की धारणा &lt;strong&gt;futuristic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए,&lt;strong&gt; future tense &lt;/strong&gt;का उपयोग किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simple future tense&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में &lt;strong&gt;passive verb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;रूप &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;will / shall + be before the past participle form of the verb&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; कर बनाया जाता है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: I will be helped by her.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;daughter-in-laws&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;daughters-in-law&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;daughter-in-laws&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some &lt;strong&gt;hyphenated&lt;/strong&gt; terms are made up of a &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; and some other parts of speech. For example, &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;passer-by&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt; is made up of a noun (passer) and a preposition (by). &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Secretary-general&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt; contains a &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; (secretary) and an &lt;strong&gt;adjective&lt;/strong&gt; (general).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;With these terms, you should &lt;strong&gt;pluralize&lt;/strong&gt; only the &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​Many passer-bys stopped to look at the window display.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Many passers-by stopped to look at the window display.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She speaks very highly of both her &lt;strong&gt;daughters-in-law.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य व्याकरण की दृष्टि से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;daughter-in-laws&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; के स्थान पर &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;daughters-in-law&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;कुछ &lt;strong&gt;hyphenated&lt;/strong&gt; शब्द &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; से बने होते हैं और कुछ भाषण के अन्य भाग से। उदाहरण के लिए, &lt;em&gt;passer-by&lt;/em&gt; is made up of a noun (passer) and a preposition (by). &lt;em&gt;Secretary-general&lt;/em&gt; contains a &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; (secretary) and an &lt;strong&gt;adjective&lt;/strong&gt; (general).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इन शर्तों के साथ, आपको केवल &lt;strong&gt;Noun&lt;/strong&gt; को&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;pluralize&lt;/strong&gt; करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​Many passer-bys stopped to look at the window display.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Many passers-by stopped to look at the window display.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर&lt;strong&gt; विकल्प 3&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Strangers should not be allowed into the society complex.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Passive Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + should + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;. (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41794S&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41803S&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41812S&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;The given sentence is an example of&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;an imperative sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If someone gives a command, do request, expresses a desire or wish, suggestion, in sentences then such sentences are called an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;imperative sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The notion of the given sentence is a suggestion.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Help the poor people. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The poor people should be helped. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The subject of the given sentence is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Strangers&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;do not allow&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;should not be allowed&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41812E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41803E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_41794E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strangers should not be allowed into the society complex.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;Active Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें इसे&lt;strong&gt; Passive Voice&lt;/strong&gt; में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&lt;strong&gt; Imperative Sentence &lt;/strong&gt;का उदाहरण है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;यदि कोई वाक्य में आदेश देता है, अनुरोध करता है, इच्छा या इच्छा व्यक्त करता है, सुझाव देता है, तो ऐसे वाक्यों को&lt;strong&gt; Imperative Sentence&lt;/strong&gt; कहा जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य की धारणा सुझाव है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों की संरचना इस प्रकार है:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;V1 + Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject (Objective Case) + should + be + V3. (Passive Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Help the poor people. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The poor people should be helped. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य का &lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Stranger&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; है।&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;do not allow&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;should not be allowed&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, ऊपर वर्णित बिंदुओं के अनुसार, हम पाते हैं कि सही उत्तर &lt;strong&gt;विकल्प 1&lt;/strong&gt; है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Dishonour.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Disgrace&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;That which brings dishonour; a cause of shame or reproach.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;one mistake brought &lt;strong&gt;disgrace &lt;/strong&gt;to all his family.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Dishonour&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest word to the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Disgrace&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The synonyms of &lt;strong&gt;Disgrace &lt;/strong&gt;are&lt;strong&gt; shame, ignominy, discredit, degradation, disrepute, infamy &lt;/strong&gt;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning and examples of the given words:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Words/phrase&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Dispute&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Have a disagreement over something&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;She &lt;strong&gt;disputed &lt;/strong&gt;his claims.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Discord&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Lack of agreement or harmony&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The plan to build the highway created &lt;strong&gt;discord &lt;/strong&gt;in our community.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Disgust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Strong feelings of dislike&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;She walked out in &lt;strong&gt;disgust&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;b&gt;Ran away.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;beat a retreat&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;run&quot;&gt;run&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;away from a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;dangerous&quot;&gt;dangerous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;unpleasant&quot;&gt;unpleasant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;situation&quot;&gt;situation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;When we saw the police arriving we&lt;strong&gt; beat a hasty retreat.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The phrase &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ran away&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest phrase to the idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;beat a retreat&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Did&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use the expression &lt;strong&gt;it&amp;rsquo;s time + subject + past verb&lt;/strong&gt; form to refer to&lt;strong&gt; the present moment.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: Gosh! It&amp;rsquo;s almost midnight. &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; we &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;went &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;home.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Should have + past participle&lt;/strong&gt; talks about past events, actions that did not happen but it would be better if they had happened. A mistake or regret is implied.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: You &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;should&amp;nbsp;have checked&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;your report thoroughly before you handed it in.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the sentence, we need to use the past tense of the verb(&lt;strong&gt;did&lt;/strong&gt;) because the sentence refers to the present moment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s time&lt;/strong&gt; with&lt;strong&gt; a verb in the to-infinitive &lt;/strong&gt;form can refer to the speaker and the listener together:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: Come on&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;. It&amp;rsquo;s time to start &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;packing. We have to leave in two hours. (or&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; It&amp;rsquo;s time we started packing.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The most suitable preposition is&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;in&amp;quot;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;The expression &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;staring in the face&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is an English idiom, meaning &lt;strong&gt;something is very obvious or imminent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative;   line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;In the sentence, it implies that &lt;strong&gt;poverty was an immediate and clear problem for &amp;#39;her&amp;#39;,&lt;/strong&gt; there was no avoiding it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative;   line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative;   line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;Poverty was staring her&lt;strong&gt; in&lt;/strong&gt; the face.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative;   line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;At&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;We use at to refer to time or place. We also use it to refer to activities.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I was up&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;at&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;6 am this morning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To&lt;/strong&gt;: The preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used as an infinitive of purpose to mean &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;in order to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: I spent some money (in order) &lt;strong&gt;to &lt;/strong&gt;get some help.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;On&lt;/b&gt;: The preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;on&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; indicates that something is already in the position.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: The book is &lt;strong&gt;on &lt;/strong&gt;the table.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;On the decline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;b&gt;on the wane&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;becoming smaller, less important or less common&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Her popularity was &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;on the wane.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The phrase &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;on the wane&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest phrase to the idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;on the decline&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The erroneous part is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;have shocked everybody&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The error lies in&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Part 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Replace &lt;strong&gt;have &lt;/strong&gt;with &lt;strong&gt;has&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;As the subject&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the news&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is a singular noun, we need the helping verb according to it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;has &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct verb here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; The news in illegal activities &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;has &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;shocked everybody of&amp;nbsp;his involvement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some singular uncountable nouns end in &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ndash;s.&lt;/strong&gt; They have no plural forms. &lt;strong&gt;Examples&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;news, billiards, draughts, measles etc.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: Measles is highly contagious.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Most words ending in &amp;ndash;&lt;strong&gt;ics &lt;/strong&gt;are also usually singular uncountables and have no plurals. &lt;strong&gt;Examples&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;mathematics, physics, athletics, politics.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: Politics is a dirty game.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mathematics isn&amp;rsquo;t the easiest of all subjects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other nouns which do not change in the plural are&lt;strong&gt; craft, sheep, fish and deer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;determined to expand&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Determine to do something:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to decide to do something

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;We determined to leave at once.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the sentence, because he decided to expand his business, the correct preposition to be used here is&lt;strong&gt; to.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; He is &lt;em&gt;determined to expand &lt;/em&gt;his business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bare Infinitives (When Not Preceded by &amp;quot;To&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Most infinitives are preceded by &amp;quot;to,&amp;quot; but after certain verbs, the &amp;quot;to&amp;quot; is dropped.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most obvious example is when an infinitive follows &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;can,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;could,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;may,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;might,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;must,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;shall,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;should,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;will,&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;would&amp;quot; (i.e., a modal verb).&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example:&lt;/strong&gt; You must take a break.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3649c979-7fff-a075-3ab3-b9f8f76b329e&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The active voice of the given sentence is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;They will have finished the breakfast by nine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Future perfect tense&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86);&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Future perfect&amp;nbsp;tense&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to talk about something that will be completed before a specific time in the future.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table style=&quot;border-color:initial;border-style:none;border-width:initial;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;colgroup&gt;
	&lt;/colgroup&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(28, 234, 234); overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(28, 234, 234); overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3649c979-7fff-a075-3ab3-b9f8f76b329e&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(54, 236, 242); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Active&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;Object + will/shall + have+ been + V3&amp;nbsp;+ by + subject&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;Subject + will/shall + have&amp;nbsp;+ V&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ object.&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;padding-inline-start: 48px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The instructions given below should be followed while changing&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a passive voice&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an active&amp;nbsp;voice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Find the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject and objec&lt;/span&gt;t of the sentence and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exchange their places;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;make changes in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as well if subject and object are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Remove the preposition&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;by&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; before the agent.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Change&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;will/shall + have + been&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the passive voice into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;will/shall + have&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to make it active voice.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;At last line up the remaining part.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;So, the final sentence is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;They will have finished the breakfast by nine.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impersonal Passive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Verbs without an object (intransitive verb) normally cannot form a personal passive sentence (as there is no object that can become the subject of the passive sentence). If you want to use an intransitive verb in passive voice, you need an impersonal construction &amp;ndash; therefore this passive voice&amp;nbsp;is called &lt;strong&gt;Impersonal Passive.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: he says &amp;ndash; it is said&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It has to be seen to be believed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While changing the voice of &lt;strong&gt;an infinitive sentence,&lt;/strong&gt; we change the verb as follows;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To catch----- To be caught, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To help------&amp;nbsp;to be helped&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All the other rules remain&amp;nbsp;the same as the other passive voices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject and object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exchange their places&lt;/span&gt;; make changes in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as well if subject and object are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Always use&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the third form of the main verb(robbed)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in passive form.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;At last line up the remaining part.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;So, the final sentence is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;It has to be seen to be believed.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;b&gt;been revealed.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&lt;strong&gt; c&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;o&lt;/strong&gt;me to light&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means become widely known or evident.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;no new facts came to light&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The phrase &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;come to light&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest phrase to the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;revealed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0d2616a-7fff-0130-bb51-58e69c49c479&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;No substitution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;padding-inline-start: 48px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;T&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ha&lt;/strong&gt;n&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is a conjunction used to two comparable sentence/phrase.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: She is smarter &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;than &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;her sister.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;So, &lt;strong&gt;than &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct conjunction here in the sentence.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I &lt;/strong&gt;is a singular noun, hence, need a singular verb.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;So, &lt;strong&gt;Was &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct helping verb.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0d2616a-7fff-0130-bb51-58e69c49c479&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Thus, the given sentence is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The indirect speech of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​I asked the postman if there was a letter for me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&amp;nbsp;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); width: 350px;&quot; width=&quot;350&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;I said to the postman&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Is there a letter for me.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reporting clause&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reported speech&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the reporting speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple present tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;then all the speech&amp;nbsp;Changes to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple past&amp;nbsp;tense&lt;/span&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;is----- was&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Said to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the reporting verb changed into &lt;strong&gt;asked&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Replace&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma (,) and inverted commas (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with the conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;b&gt;if&lt;/b&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Treat reported speech as an affirmative sentence.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​So, the final sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​I asked the postman if there was a letter for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;What is Direct &amp;amp; Indirect Speech?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct speech&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; reporting the message of the speaker in the exact words as spoken by him.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct speech example&lt;/span&gt;: Maya said, &amp;quot;I am busy now&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;: reporting the message of the speaker in our own words&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect speech example&lt;/span&gt;: Maya said that she was busy then.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Her health has being&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;The words &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;being&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;been&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; are sometimes confused,&amp;nbsp;the word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;been&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; is always used after &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;have&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; whereas &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;being&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; is never used after &amp;lsquo;have&amp;rsquo;. It is used after &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Been&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the past participle of the verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and is usually used with the perfect aspect&amp;nbsp;with &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;have&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; in all its forms i.e.&lt;strong&gt; had and has&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: I have &lt;em&gt;been &lt;/em&gt;busy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;being&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the present participle of the verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and can be used with the continuous form of the verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is all its forms i.e. &lt;em&gt;am, is, was, are and were.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: When I arrived at the scene of the accident the victim was &lt;strong&gt;being &lt;/strong&gt;placed in an ambulance.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;I don&amp;#39;t know why but John is &lt;strong&gt;being &lt;/strong&gt;really difficult today.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;Her health has &lt;strong&gt;been &lt;/strong&gt;steadily improving since she started practising yoga.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Being as a noun&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;being&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; can also be used as a noun.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: A human being.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Being as a gerund&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;being&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; can be used as a gerund which is a type of noun.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;: Do all actors like being famous?&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His being clumsy caused the accident.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-28c0372f-7fff-10ff-c6dc-cdeb0c72df4f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The passive voice of the given sentence is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;May God bless you with good health!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Optative sentence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;to shows a prayer or a wish. It starts with &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;may&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; or &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;wish&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table style=&quot;border-color:initial;border-style:none;border-width:initial;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;colgroup&gt;
	&lt;/colgroup&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Active&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;May + Subject + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ object.&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;May + Object + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by + subject&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The instructions given below should be followed while changing&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;an optative sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a passive voice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Find&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the subject and object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exchange their places&lt;/span&gt;; make changes in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as well if subject and object are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Use the preposition &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;by&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; before the agent.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The place of the optative word &amp;#39;may&amp;#39; remains the same.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Always use&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the third form of the main verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in passive form.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;At last line up the remaining part.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;So, the final sentence is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;May God bless you with good health!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-28c0372f-7fff-10ff-c6dc-cdeb0c72df4f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The passive voice of the given sentence is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The man was robbed of all his possessions by someone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38; padding: 0pt 0pt 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-28c0372f-7fff-10ff-c6dc-cdeb0c72df4f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 164px; height: 44px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;44&quot; src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KYAs8NFITO519GCjgqJIU57PsbhfsONnSnQPeVegpSpdV96qm4Cfyz8h5vTxC1cihAvWNCXYPmZ2QzrFiK6QkKirFcN-zJlRN6cw7Chlw5w-F9wUJUoFeKvbb1H4RMKgfJ72_RMS&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;164&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple Past Tense&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;simple past&lt;/strong&gt; is a verb tense that is used to talk about things that happened or existed before now.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table style=&quot;border-width: initial; border-style: none; border-color: initial;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;colgroup&gt;
	&lt;/colgroup&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(28, 234, 234); overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-28c0372f-7fff-10ff-c6dc-cdeb0c72df4f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(54, 236, 242); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Active&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(28, 234, 234); overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-28c0372f-7fff-10ff-c6dc-cdeb0c72df4f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(54, 236, 242); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Passive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 0pt;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;Subject + V&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5px;&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;+ object&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;padding: 5pt; border-width: 1pt; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;Object+ was//were&amp;nbsp;+V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;+ by+ subject?&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The instructions given below should be followed while changing&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a simple past sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a passive voice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Find&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the subject and object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exchange their places&lt;/span&gt;; make changes in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cases&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as well if subject and object are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Use preposition &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;by&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; before the agent.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Use an appropriate&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;helping verb(was) in the passive form at the start of the sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;according to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the tense of the active form. (Simple past- was//were +v3)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Always use&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the third form of the main verb(robbed)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in passive form.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;At last line up the remaining part.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;So, the final sentence is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;The man was robbed of all his possessions by someone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The indirect speech of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;Mother suggested that we should go to the hills for a vacation.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Mother said to us,&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Let us go to the hills for a vacation&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reporting clause&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reported speech&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The sentence which is used to convey&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a command, a request, or a forbiddance&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an imperative sentence&lt;/span&gt;. So the given speech is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an imperative one&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;While changing the narration of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an imperative sentence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;we need to follow the given steps-&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Change&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in reporting clause into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ordered/forbade/suggested/advised/requested etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;b&gt;let us&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;indicates that the sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a kind of suggestion&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;so we used&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;suggested&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;said to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li aria-level=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
		&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Replace&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;comma (,)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;inverted commas (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with the conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;that&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;​​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​​So, the correct sentence is&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mother suggested that we should go to the hills for a vacation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Words like&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;forbade, prohibit, interdict, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;have &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;not&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; hidden in their meanings. So, the use of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;not&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; with these words should be&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;avoided&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li aria-level=&quot;1&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;He forbade me to have ice cream.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Or&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He asked me not to have ice cream.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;only mistake&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add the before only in &lt;strong&gt;option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is used to refer to specific or particular nouns.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, adverb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;only&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; specify the noun &lt;strong&gt;mistake&lt;/strong&gt;, hence we need an article &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;the&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; before it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is &lt;strong&gt;the only&lt;/strong&gt; mistake he has made in the dictation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Refute.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Contradict&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to say that something is wrong or not true&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex:&lt;em&gt; T&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;hese instructions seem to contradict previous ones.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Refute&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest word to the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Contradict&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning and examples of the given words:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Words/phrase&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Refute&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Overthrow by argument,&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The speaker &lt;strong&gt;refuted &lt;/strong&gt;his opponent&amp;#39;s arguments.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Agree&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;be in agreement&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;I can&amp;#39;t &lt;strong&gt;agree &lt;/strong&gt;with you&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shorten&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Make shorter than originally intended&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;He &lt;strong&gt;shortened &lt;/strong&gt;his trip due to illness&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Advise&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Give advice to&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The teacher &lt;strong&gt;advises &lt;/strong&gt;troubled students&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Your&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Before a &lt;strong&gt;gerund&lt;/strong&gt;, we need &lt;strong&gt;a possessive adjective&lt;/strong&gt; of noun or pronoun.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;I didn&amp;#39;t like &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;his &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;going to New York without me.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;granting &lt;/strong&gt;is a gerund noun and we need &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;possessive&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;case &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;your&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; before it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer&lt;/strong&gt;: I request the favour of &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;your &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;granting me two days&amp;#39; leave.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using the possessive before a gerund&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We often put&lt;strong&gt; a noun or pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; in front of a &lt;strong&gt;gerund &lt;/strong&gt;to show who or what is doing the action in the gerund. This noun or pronoun is called the subject of the gerund. In formal writing, the subject of the gerund should be in the possessive form:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your &lt;/strong&gt;leaving early was a wise decision.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;We celebrated &lt;strong&gt;Gord&amp;rsquo;s &lt;/strong&gt;winning the contest.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Natalie objected to my borrowing &lt;strong&gt;her &lt;/strong&gt;hockey stick.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sums up to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;boils down&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means &lt;em&gt;reduce the volume of a liquid by boiling. Or &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to be the main reason for something or the most basic part of something&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;they boil down the syrup until it is very thick&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The phrase &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sums up to&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the closest phrase to the idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;boils down&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, by reading the above explanation we find that the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;AECBDF&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 16.1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;connects the sentence A&amp;nbsp;as&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;but&amp;#39; contrasting what is mentioned in A&lt;/span&gt;. Hence, E&amp;nbsp;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first part.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 16.1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt; further connects&amp;nbsp;the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence &amp;#39;E&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with the conjunction &amp;#39;so&amp;#39; which act as a result of sentence E.&amp;nbsp;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;C&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;second part.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt; and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;D&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are co-related where &lt;b&gt;sentence B&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;starts a new clause and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;part D&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;completes that. Hence, &lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;third and&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;fourth parts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the sentence respectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 16.1px;&quot;&gt;The correct sentence after rearranging the parts:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;One day I went to school with four rupees in my pocket to pay the school fees,&amp;nbsp;But the teacher who was to collect the fees was absent. So, I was told that the fees would be collected the next day. All through the day, the coins sat quietly in my pocket&amp;nbsp;When school got over, the coins in my pocket began to speak.&amp;nbsp;They said that money was meant to be spent on good things like hot &amp;lsquo;jalebis&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hint-text-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hint&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Rules to Solve the Para Jumbles:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Read the sentences&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;attentively and try to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;comprehend the idea or theme of the sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;eliminate the irrelevant options.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Try to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;identify the opening(&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;independent sentence) and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;closing sentences&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;( concluding sentence).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Try to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;identify the mandatory pairs&lt;/span&gt;. Two sentences can be connected through various connectors and other determinants.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;No substitution&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; when the reason or purpose is a &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. Use &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;for&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; when the reason or purpose is a &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I bought a present to give&lt;strong&gt; to&lt;/strong&gt; Sarah on her birthday. (&lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I bought a present &lt;strong&gt;for &lt;/strong&gt;Sarah&amp;rsquo;s birthday. (&lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, the reason is a verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;go&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, hence we need preposition&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;to&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;after &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; we generally use&lt;strong&gt; base form of verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the above sentence is &lt;strong&gt;correct&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The indirect speech of the given sentence is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I asked my daughter why she was angry with me.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); width: 350px;&quot; width=&quot;350&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;I&amp;nbsp;said to my daughter,&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Why are you angry with me?&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reporting clause&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reported speech&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the reporting speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple present Tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;then all the speech&amp;nbsp;Changes to the respective&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Past tense&lt;/span&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;is/are/am----- was/were&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Said to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the reporting verb changed into &lt;strong&gt;asked&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma (,) and inverted commas (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as the reported speech is an interrogative sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;second person in the reported speech(you)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;changes according to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the object of reporting clause(my daughter).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;You&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;changes&amp;nbsp;to &amp;#39;&lt;b&gt;She&lt;/b&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​So, the final sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I asked my daughter why she was angry with me.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Can&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Could&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;May&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Might&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Must&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Had to/Would have to&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Could&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Could&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Would&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Would&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Ought to&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Ought to&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Might&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Might&lt;br /&gt;
			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Won&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We generally use &lt;strong&gt;past tense &lt;/strong&gt;when a specific time of past is mentioned in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;1945 &lt;/strong&gt;indicates the past time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We need&lt;strong&gt; a second form of verb &lt;/strong&gt;in the &lt;strong&gt;past tense.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;won &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt; The Allies won the war in 1945.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Much of us&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Much&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used when we are speaking about a singular noun. &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Many&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used when we are speaking about a plural noun.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I don&amp;#39;t have&lt;strong&gt; much &lt;/strong&gt;time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;We have &lt;strong&gt;many &lt;/strong&gt;friends, in many countries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;Us &lt;/strong&gt;is &lt;strong&gt;plural pronoun&lt;/strong&gt;, so the use of &lt;strong&gt;Much &lt;/strong&gt;is incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; option 3 &lt;/strong&gt;is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence: &lt;/strong&gt;Many of us lack the important virtue of patience.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;kind of book&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;phrase&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot;kind of&amp;quot; does not take a definite article after it&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; no matter whether the noun that follows is countable or uncountable.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of the &lt;em&gt;article&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the&amp;#39; after&lt;/strong&gt; the phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;kind of&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;incorrect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence the&lt;em&gt; article&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; must be &lt;strong&gt;omitted&lt;/strong&gt; to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;What &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;kind of book&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; do you want?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;In English there are three articles&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;strong&gt; a, an, and the.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Articles are used before nouns or noun equivalents and are a type of adjective.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The definite article &lt;strong&gt;(the) &lt;/strong&gt;is used &lt;strong&gt;before a noun&lt;/strong&gt; to indicate that &lt;strong&gt;the identity of the noun is known to the reader.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; This is &lt;strong&gt;the highest building&lt;/strong&gt; in New York.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;are leaving the room&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In part &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;are leaving the room&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;the usage of &amp;#39;are leaving&amp;#39; is incorrect Instead, use &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;leave&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the rule of grammar, the usage of present continuous is correct when we want to use a temporary action but in the given, there is no temporary action is used. Hence, we need to use present indefinite tense. Also, in the main clause, the verb is in the present tense hence, we need to use a present tense in the subordinate clause too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct sentence is-&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Please switch off all the lights&lt;strong&gt; before you leave&lt;/strong&gt; the room.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;ambiguous&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apparent-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;clearly visible or understood; obvious.(स्पष्ट रूप से दिखाई या समझी जाने वाली; ज़ाहिर।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Absurd-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;wildly unreasonable, illogical, or inappropriate. (बेतहाशा अनुचित, अतार्किक या अनुचित।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambiguous-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;open to more than one interpretation; not having one obvious meaning.(एक से अधिक व्याख्या के लिए खुला; एक स्पष्ट अर्थ नहीं होना।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Axiom-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a statement or proposition which is regarded as being established, accepted, or self-evidently true. (एक कथन या प्रस्ताव जिसे स्थापित, स्वीकृत या स्व-स्पष्ट रूप से सत्य माना जाता है।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, according to the meanings of the given words, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Mother said to the children, &amp;ldquo;Stop playing now.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in Indirect speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, In Indirect speech the usage of &amp;#39;infinitive&amp;#39; is given in the sentence, hence, from this we can say that the given reported speech should be an imperative one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When you give someone an order, you use the imperative form, which means using just the verb without a subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, in Direct speech the reported verb will become &amp;#39;said to&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;that&amp;#39; will be removed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adverb &amp;#39;then&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;now&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct speech is-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Mother said to the children, &amp;quot;Stop playing now.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;BADC&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence starts with&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;B&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;as it contains the &lt;strong&gt;subject &amp;#39;Mahendra&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;and also tells us &lt;strong&gt;where he works&lt;/strong&gt;, giving the passage a proper&lt;strong&gt; introduction&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;Mahendra was a junior supervisor in a firm.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; follows&lt;strong&gt; B &lt;/strong&gt;further describing &lt;strong&gt;what his job was and what all he has to do their&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;His job was to keep an eye on the activities at the work site.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt; giving us &lt;strong&gt;more details regarding Mahendra&amp;#39;s job&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;The work sites changed often so he had to move from place to place.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally, &lt;strong&gt;sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; serves as the &lt;strong&gt;conclusion&lt;/strong&gt; of the passage telling us &lt;strong&gt;where all Mahendra had worded in all this time&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;So far, he had worked at stone quarries, coal mines, construction sites and chemical plants.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;BADC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The passage after rearranging the sentence will be:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Mahendra was a junior supervisor in a firm. His job was to keep an eye on the activities at the work site. The work sites changed often so he had to move from place to place. So far, he had worked at stone quarries, coal mines, construction sites and chemical plants.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Colleagues&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agents-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who acts on behalf of another person or group. (एक व्यक्ति जो किसी अन्य व्यक्ति या समूह की ओर से कार्य करता है।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rivals&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;a person or thing competing with another for the same objective or for superiority in the same field of activity. (एक ही उद्देश्य के लिए या गतिविधि के एक ही क्षेत्र में श्रेष्ठता के लिए दूसरे के साथ प्रतिस्पर्धा करने वाला व्यक्ति या वस्तु।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friends-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person with whom one has a bond of mutual affection, typically one exclusive of sexual or family relations. (एक व्यक्ति जिसके साथ आपसी स्नेह का बंधन है, आमतौर पर यौन या पारिवारिक संबंधों में से एक।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Colleagues-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person with whom one works in a profession or business (एक व्यक्ति जिसके साथ कोई पेशा या व्यवसाय में काम करता है)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, according to the meanings, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;He says that some goods are of poor quality.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The given sentence is Direct speech.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb of the sentence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Says&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is in the present tense, hence, the tense of the sentence will not be changed according to the rule of grammar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the whole indirect speech will be in the &lt;strong&gt;Present Tense.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In place of double quotes, we need to use&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;that&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject and reported speech will be the same.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So the correct answer is Option 3 i.e. &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;He says that some goods are of poor quality.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;listen to what&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given phrase is to be replaced with&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;listen to what&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s the difference between Hear and Listen.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hear means &amp;#39;Get to know or become aware of, usually accidentally&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Listen means &amp;#39;Pay attention to a sound&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, &amp;#39;The speaker&amp;#39; wants the people to pay attention to the words which will be uttered by the subject &amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So the correct answer is Option 2.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct sentence is-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Please &lt;strong&gt;listen to what&lt;/strong&gt; I am saying&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;theologian&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;theorist-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person concerned with the theoretical aspects of a subject; a theoretician. {किसी विषय के सैद्धांतिक पहलुओं से संबंधित व्यक्ति; एक सिद्धांतकार।}&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;theologian&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;a person who engages or is an expert in theology {एक व्यक्ति जो धर्मशास्त्र में संलग्न है या विशेषज्ञ है}&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;atheist-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person who disbelieves or lacks belief in the existence of God or gods. {एक व्यक्ति जो भगवान या देवताओं के अस्तित्व में विश्वास नहीं करता है या विश्वास नहीं करता है।}&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;theist-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person who believes in the existence of a god or gods, specifically of a creator who intervenes in the universe. {एक व्यक्ति जो ईश्वर या देवताओं के अस्तित्व में विश्वास करता है, विशेष रूप से एक निर्माता का जो ब्रह्मांड में हस्तक्षेप करता है।}&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, according to the meanings of the given words the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The maid said to me, &amp;ldquo;Can I get you a glass of juice?&amp;rdquo;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is Indirect Speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject of the sentence is &amp;#39;The maid&amp;#39; and the reported verb is &amp;#39;asked&amp;#39; which is going to be changed into &amp;#39;asked&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, by looking at&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;If&amp;#39; we can say that the given sentence is an interrogative sentence.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb asked will be replaced by &amp;#39;said&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunctions &amp;#39;whether/why&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;if&amp;#39; are replaced by the comma and inverted commas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The tense of reported speech is changed only when the reporting verb is in the past tense.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The said to me, &amp;quot;Can I get you a glass of Juice?&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;ACDB&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of&lt;strong&gt; sentence jumble.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence starts with &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;A&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;as it contains the &lt;strong&gt;subject &amp;#39;The flute seller&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; and&lt;em&gt; his whereabouts&lt;/em&gt;, giving the passage a proper &lt;strong&gt;introduction&lt;/strong&gt; -&lt;em&gt; The flute seller stands in a corner of the square near the hotel.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; follows&lt;strong&gt; A&lt;/strong&gt; adding details about &lt;strong&gt;what the flute seller was holding in his hands&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;In his hand is a pole from which protrude about fifty flutes in all directions.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt; describing &lt;strong&gt;what the flutes are made up of&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;They are all made from hollow bamboo stems.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally,&lt;strong&gt; sentence B&lt;/strong&gt; is used as the &lt;strong&gt;conclusion&lt;/strong&gt; telling us &lt;strong&gt;what he was actually doing there&lt;/strong&gt; -&lt;em&gt; From time to time, he stands the pole on the ground, selects a flute and plays a tune.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence the correct sequence is &lt;strong&gt;ACBD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The passage after rearranging the sentences will be:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The flute seller stands in a corner of the square near the hotel. In his hand is a pole from which protrude about fifty flutes in all directions. They are all made from hollow bamboo stems. From time to time, he stands the pole on the ground, selects a flute and plays a tune.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;AEBDCF&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; talks about the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;several daughters&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; of the King and Queen of Siam, &lt;em&gt;directly connecting&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sentence E&lt;/strong&gt; which talks about&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; the Queen who gets confused remembering so many names&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B&lt;/strong&gt; follows sentence &lt;strong&gt;E &lt;/strong&gt;telling us &lt;em&gt;the names of the daughters of the Kind and Queen.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;follows&lt;/strong&gt; sentence&lt;strong&gt; B respectively&lt;/strong&gt;, as in sentence &lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt; we get to know that&lt;em&gt; the King gifted each of his daughters a green parrot on his birthday&lt;/em&gt; and in sentence &lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt; we get to know that &lt;em&gt;the princesses were proud of their gift and spent most of their time teaching the parrots to talk.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence the correct sequence is &lt;strong&gt;AEBDCF.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;overflowed its banks&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given phrase is to be replaced with&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;overflowed its banks&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verb forms of &amp;#39;overflow&amp;#39; are- overflowed (past tense) and overflowed (past participle).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, in the given sentence &amp;#39;It&amp;#39;s&amp;#39; is incorrect we need to use the possessive case i.e. &amp;#39;Its&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The contraction of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;it&amp;#39;s&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;It is&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct sentence is- &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The river &lt;strong&gt;overflowed its banks &lt;/strong&gt;in the monsoon.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Free food grains are being distributed among the poor by the government.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject of the sentence is &amp;#39;The government&amp;#39; and the object of the sentence is &amp;#39;food grains&amp;#39;. &amp;#39;among the poor&amp;#39; is a prepositional phrase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the passive, the subject of the sentence becomes the object and the object of the sentence becomes the subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, the verb of the sentence is &amp;#39;is distributing&amp;#39; which is in the present continuous tense. So, in the passive voice, it becomes &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;be (forms) +being+ V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Also, the prepositional phrase to be written after the main verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct passive sentence is-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Free food grains are being distributed among the poor by the government.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;went abroad&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given phrase is to be replaced with &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;went abroad&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence after the main verb ask a question &amp;#39;He went where?&amp;#39; hence, we need to use an adverb instead of the infinitive.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Foreign&amp;#39; is an adjective&amp;nbsp;that means-&amp;nbsp;relating to or originating in or characteristic of another place or part of the world. After the preposition &amp;#39;to&amp;#39; we need to use a verb or a noun.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Abroad is an adverb that means-&amp;nbsp;To or in a foreign country.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct sentence is-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;He went &lt;strong&gt;abroad&lt;/strong&gt; for higher education.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The incorrect part is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has fallen in love&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the part &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;has fallen in love&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;phrase&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Once upon a time&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;at some time in the past&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; (used as a conventional opening of a story).&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; He was a famous actor &lt;strong&gt;once upon a time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If something was&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;once upon a time&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; it is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;certainly in the past and complete&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, so it is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;normally followed by the simple past&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;has&amp;nbsp;fallen&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; must be replaced with&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;fell&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Once upon a time, a beautiful princess &lt;strong&gt;fell&lt;/strong&gt; in love with a poor farmer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;He warned his employee not to provoke him unnecessarily.&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;When the reported speech is in an&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;imperative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;form, we follow the steps given below:

	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Change the sentence in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;from&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;imperative&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The reporting verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;said to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is converted into &lt;strong&gt;warn&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ed&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;He is giving a warning to his employee.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;tense&lt;/strong&gt; of reported speech is changed only when the &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; is in the &lt;strong&gt;past tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;To infinitive&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;used in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;comma&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted commas&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;followed by the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1st form of the verb.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Do not provoke&amp;#39; &lt;/span&gt;changes&amp;nbsp;into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;not to provoke&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The first person pronoun &amp;#39;me&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;him&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So, the correct sentence will be:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;He warned his employee not to provoke him unnecessarily.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous spelling is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Suprimacy&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct spelling of the word is &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Supremacy&amp;#39; that means &amp;#39;Power to dominate or defeat&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see an example-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The company has begun to challenge the &lt;strong&gt;supremac&lt;/strong&gt;y of the current leading manufacturers in the textiles industry.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;hostage&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dealer-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Someone who purchases and maintains an inventory of goods to be sold&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guest-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;A visitor to whom hospitality is extended&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Host-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;A technical name for the bread used in the service of Mass or Holy Communion&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hostage-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;A prisoner who is held by one party to insure that another party will meet specified terms&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, according to the meanings of the given words, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;The young man said, &amp;quot;What a great feast it is!&amp;quot;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;basic rules&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for changing or&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;converting indirect speech into direct speech&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;commas,&amp;nbsp;inverted commas and exclamatory mark&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;added&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;direct speech&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, the &lt;strong&gt;exclamatory phrase&amp;nbsp;or word (interjection)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;replaces&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;exclaimed with joy, sorrow, regret, surprise, contempt etc&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;he &lt;strong&gt;full stop (.)&lt;/strong&gt; in indirect speech,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;changes into the exclamation mark (!)&lt;/strong&gt; in direct speech.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;conjunction&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;past tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;format&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject&amp;nbsp;+ was +&amp;nbsp;Object&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;present tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;format &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject&amp;nbsp;+ is +&amp;nbsp;Object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct sentence will be:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The young man said, &amp;quot;What a great feast it is!&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;am very busy&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the idiom&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;have my hands full&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to be so busy that you do not have time to do anything else&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see an example-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I&amp;#39;d love to help but I&amp;#39;ve got &lt;strong&gt;my hands full&lt;/strong&gt; organizing the school play.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;मुहावरे का अर्थ&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;have my hands full&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;है&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;इतना व्यस्त होना कि आपके पास कुछ और करने का समय न हो&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;आइए एक उदाहरण देखते हैं-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I&amp;#39;d love to help but I&amp;#39;ve got &lt;strong&gt;my hands full &lt;/strong&gt;organizing the school play.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;तो सही उत्तर&lt;strong&gt; विकल्प 1 है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;at the height of activity&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the idiom&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;in full swing&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;at a stage when the level of activity is at its highest&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see an example-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The economic recovery is now &lt;strong&gt;in full swing.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;मुहावरे का अर्थ&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;in full swing&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;है&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;ऐसे चरण में जब गतिविधि का स्तर अपने उच्चतम स्तर पर हो&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;आइए एक उदाहरण देखें
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The economic recovery is now&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in full swing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;अत: सही उत्तर विकल्प 1 है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Sania told me that the next day was her convocation.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given question&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;told&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;speech has an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be added and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&lt;strong&gt; inverted&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;my&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;her&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because the first person&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are changed according to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;is&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Lastly, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;adverb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;tomorrow&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;the next day&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sania told me that the next day was her convocation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Change in adverbs&amp;nbsp;and determines in Direct To Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Adverbs in &amp;#39;direct speech&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Adverbs in &amp;#39;indirect speech&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Now&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Then&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Today&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Here&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;There&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;This&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;These&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Those&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Ago&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Before&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Today&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Tomorrow&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The next day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The incorrect part is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;elder than&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the part&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;elder than&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We need to remember &lt;strong&gt;older than&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct form.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;He is &lt;strong&gt;older than&lt;/strong&gt; all his friends.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;But usually, &lt;strong&gt;among siblings &lt;/strong&gt;we generally &lt;strong&gt;use &amp;quot;elder&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;elder&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;always followed by&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;em&gt;preposition&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;to&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;My son John is two years &lt;strong&gt;elder to&lt;/strong&gt; my daughter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So remember the point- &lt;strong&gt;Older than / Elder to.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;than&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; must be replaced with &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Parul is ten years &lt;strong&gt;elder to&lt;/strong&gt; her sibling.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;The football tournament will be cancelled this year&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;subject &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;of the given sentence is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;They&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;and the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;object &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the football tournament&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;In the passive, the subject of the sentence becomes the object and the object of the sentence becomes the subject.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;will&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; indicates &lt;em&gt;simple future.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;passive verb form&lt;/em&gt; in the&lt;em&gt; simple future tense&lt;/em&gt; is made by putting &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;will / shall + be before the past participle form of the verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;will cancel&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;becomes &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;will be cancelled&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In passive voice &lt;strong&gt;we may omit the agent&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;(They)&lt;/em&gt; because &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;we don&amp;#39;t know who they are, or it&amp;#39;s implied or unimportant, or we&amp;#39;d rather not say.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct passive sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; The football tournament will be cancelled this year.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
